title: Wildlife_Emphasis_Areas
name: Wildlife_Emphasis_Areas
description:
Draft Resource Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement, published December 2012
Theme: Core Wildlife Areas. Changed name to Wildlife Emphasis Areas, 2011 11. Core Wildlife Areas are areas with high wildlife areas and significance for wildlife species including sage-grouse, pronghorn antelope, mule deer, elk, prairie dog, and kit fox. 
Description: Core wildlife areas by alternative.
Vintage: 2010. 
Source: Data was derived from GJFO GIS data, especially wildlife data from CDOW, 2010. T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\wildlife\2010 CDOW Pronghorn Data.lyr
T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\wildlife\2010 CDOW elk data.lyr
T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\wildlife\2010 CDOW kit fox overall range.lyr
T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\wildlife\2010 CDOW mule deer data.lyr
T:\CO\GIS\gisdata\field_offices\gjfo\wildlife\2010 CDOW White Tailed Prairie Dog Data.lyr
Capture Methodology: Copy/Paste from 2010 CDOW GIS data, limited to GJFO BLM land.
Steward: Doug Diekman  GIS Specialist 970-244-3087
Attribute: See Entity Attribute for further details. 
Reliability: As per GJFO GIS data. 
Intended use: Cartographic use for display of public lands included in plan revision. 
Quality Control: GJFO GIS staff. 
Projection: UTM zone 13, Datum NAD 1983, Spheroid Clark 1866 
Agency Contact: Doug Diekman, GIS Specialist 970-244-3087 
NO WARRANTY IS MADE BY THE BUREAU OF LAND MANAGEMENT FOR THE USE 
OF THE DATA FOR PURPOSES NOT INTENDED BY THE BUREAU.
